54:19                                   _s_t_r_á_n_k_a_]
May (we all find love)...
May...

once upon a time, there was a boy. Nice one, trustworthy, friendly and
faithful. But (there is this but) there was no one who could help him bear the
burden of responsibility – a gift called life. Sands of time washed away all
his sadness, again and again. He enjoyed his life since the life itself is the
greatest miracle ever created and only God knows its meaning...

In the night, when moon is full and his beautiful light kindles a fire in the
lovers’ eyes, sparkling in the darkness of the night, he is sad again. It
doesn’t matter the wind of love is all around him and minstrels sing that
beautiful songs about love and eternity, he does not care. Because there is no
one who could accept his love and tell him: „You are my beloved one.“

How sad is life without love... like a beautiful garden full of flowers in the
middle of desert. Overwhelming power of love bind in one point, how sad is
that. If I could, if I might... how beautiful is a woman who loves you more
than anything else.

If you have such a woman, caress her. Trust me, you have reached eternity.
Because those who were loved, just once, those will never be forgotten.

A friend of mine told me: Lovers are like angels with one wing. They can fly
only if they join their hearts. Only two hearts can reunite two wings and the
magic of love will continue. May we all find our lost part...

May...

it is not only a month. It is a word of wisdom, word of indefatigable power.
It is a word, a month of love.

May we all find our true love one day.

Good night and may the angels be with you :)
